The ups and downs of healing are hard. One moment your fine and then the nexts you’re curled up into a ball crying. 

So you take it day by day. Handle the waves as they come and continue to put one foot in-front of the other, even if you had to take 3 steps back. 

Eventually you’ll be able to look back and be proud. You’ll smile at all that you’ve accomplished and moved through. 

One thing I’ve learned through all of this.. is it doesn’t last forever. It passes, time goes by and you become stronger for all you’ve gone through. So keep moving forward, because eventually it’ll be your time to Thrive 🫶

SAVE this post. #3 is the most important!! 

1. Batching your content is going to save your mental sanity. Take 1 day out of the week to make 5-10 pieces of work. Your future self will thank you! 

2. Everything is content. Film your life. B Roll is so valuable! 

3. Make sure you are sharing the things you love. For example if you don’t connect, resinate, or have a purpose behind your work.. creating content is going to drain you! Make it matter and stop paying attention to those numbers. Which brings me to…. 👇

4. 🛑Stop paying attention to the numbers. They will rise and they will fall. Those numbers do NOT determine your worth! (I’m still trying to remind myself of this) 

5. Make sure you schedule in breaks. Make sundays family days Or Fridays are just for you and your boo! I do t care What day you pick, just pick a day for breaks. 

#contentcreator #contentcreation #advicefromacontentcreator

Struggling every day 
to just be able to do normal things like make your kids lunch and take them to school. Waking up in the morning praying it’s going to be a good day. So you can do all the things your mind wants you to do. But sometimes your body has different plans. Never knowing when a flare up is going to happen and trying to walk that thin line of not pissing it off. Then you flare up, feel like a failure and all your plans go out the window. You have to rest but you’re sick of fucking resting. You just want to live 
your life. #autoimmunedisease #chronicpain #chronicfatigue #chronicfatiguesyndrome #mecfs
